The paper deals with the problem of universal sequence prediction, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the concept of randomness, which is a fundamental concept in computer science and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Hellinger distance as a measure of closeness between distributions suggests a connection to statistics and data analysis (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents negative and positive results on the convergence of semimeasures, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
